      "bookFormat": "AudiobookFormat",

      "name": "PLC Programming for Industrial Automation: A Practical Guide with Examples and Case Studies",

      "description": "<p><b>Master PLC Programming and Industrial Automation with Real-World Examples<\/b><\/p><p>From manufacturing plants and conveyor systems to HVAC control and smart packaging lines, <b>Programmable Logic Controllers (PLCs)<\/b> are the backbone of modern automation. This comprehensive guide takes you step by step from PLC basics to advanced applications, equipping you with the skills to design, program, and troubleshoot industrial systems.<\/p>What You\u2019ll Learn Inside:<p>\u2705 <b>PLC Fundamentals<\/b> \u2013 Understand PLC hardware, inputs\/outputs, communication, and software tools.<br \/>\u2705 <b>Programming Languages<\/b> \u2013 Learn Ladder Logic, Structured Text, and Function Block programming (IEC 61131-3 standard).<br \/>\u2705 <b>Timers, Counters, and Data Handling<\/b> \u2013 Build precise and reliable control sequences.<br \/>\u2705 <b>Analog I\/O & HMI\/SCADA Integration<\/b> \u2013 Work with sensors, actuators, and operator interfaces.<br \/>\u2705 <b>Safety, Interlocks & Error Handling<\/b> \u2013 Design safe, fail-proof control logic.<br \/>\u2705 <b>Advanced Topics<\/b> \u2013 Explore Industry 4.0, IoT integration, OPC UA, MQTT, edge computing, and predictive maintenance.<br \/>\u2705 <b>Case Studies<\/b> \u2013 Hands-on examples including conveyor belt control, traffic lights, tank level management, packaging\/sorting, and HVAC automation.<\/p>Why This Book?<ul><li><p>Covers <b>popular brands<\/b>: Siemens, Allen-Bradley, and Schneider.<\/p><\/li><li><p>Written in a <b>clear, practical style<\/b> with diagrams, ladder logic, and structured examples.<\/p><\/li><li><p>Includes <b>troubleshooting guides, coding standards, and quick references<\/b> for the field.<\/p><\/li><li><p>Bridges <b>theory and practice<\/b>, making it useful for beginners and working professionals alike.<\/p><\/li><\/ul><p>Whether you\u2019re an <b>engineering student, technician, or automation professional<\/b>, this book will serve as your <b>complete reference and training manual<\/b> for PLC programming.<\/p><p>Take control of automation today \u2014 and prepare for the future of smart factories, Industry 4.0, and AI-driven industrial systems.<\/p>",

